BBC.Later.Live.with.Jools.Holland.S45E06.1080i.h264-NX

BBC 2 HD 21st Oct 2014
10pm to 10:30pm S45E06 Live

Joining Jools on the show and making their debut on the programme is Dublin's U2, who are performing songs from their new album Songs of Innocence. From London, and making his solo debut on the show, Sam Smith has had one of the best-selling albums of the year with his debut In the Lonely Hour. From New York City, Interpol last performed on the show in 2004 and return to play songs from their recent fifth studio album El Pintor. From Arizona comes Nika Roza Danilova, also known as Zola Jesus, who makes her UK television debut on the show performing tracks from her latest LP Taiga. Brothers Dave and Phil Alvin from California's seminal band the Blasters get together for the first time in almost 30 years to play tribute acoustically to blues legend Big Bill Broonzy, with songs from their album Common Ground.
